cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper focuses on improving the performance of data-driven prediction models for autonomous robotics, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of active learning approaches (cs.AI) and model-based formulations of curiosity (cs.CV) to optimize sampling strategies for training data. Additionally, the paper presents a validation dataset of action-conditioned video of robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY).
